abstract: A week after internet rumors started circulating about Christine Blasey Ford, misinformation is still spreading about her and two other women.
snippet: A week after internet rumors started circulating about Christine Blasey Ford, misinformation is still spreading about her and two other women.
lead_paragraph: Last week, after Christine Blasey Ford publicly accused Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh, the Supreme Court nominee, of sexual assault, a torrent of false and misleading allegations about Dr. Blasey surfaced online, many of them originating on social media.

headline_main: California Today: For Jerry Brown, the Past Informs the Future

abstract: More than 50 years later, Freedom Summer 1964 veterans return to the south to help a new generation of leaders register voters.
snippet: More than 50 years later, Freedom Summer 1964 veterans return to the south to help a new generation of leaders register voters.
lead_paragraph: OXFORD, Miss. — The first time Howard Kirschenbaum registered voters in Mississippi was during the summer of 1964, when he was arrested and thrown in jail. The second time was on Tuesday, after returning to the Southern state more than a half-century later to support a new generation of voting rights activists.

abstract: Mr. Cosby was sentenced to serve three to 10 years for drugging and sexually assaulting Andrea Constand. He said he would appeal the conviction.
snippet: Mr. Cosby was sentenced to serve three to 10 years for drugging and sexually assaulting Andrea Constand. He said he would appeal the conviction.
lead_paragraph: NORRISTOWN, Pa. — Bill Cosby, who for years dodged accusations that he had preyed on women while brightening America’s living rooms as a beloved father figure, left a courtroom in handcuffs on Tuesday after he was sentenced to three to 10 years in prison for sexually assaulting a woman in his home.

abstract: The Tampa Bay Rays, who can no longer make the playoffs, had sparked a summer turnaround by experimenting with the order of their pitchers.
snippet: The Tampa Bay Rays, who can no longer make the playoffs, had sparked a summer turnaround by experimenting with the order of their pitchers.
lead_paragraph: ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. — In June, when their grand experiment was in its nascent stages, the Tampa Bay Rays made a full commitment to the reimagining of their pitching staff when the Yankees arrived in town.

abstract: Can seven insurgent State Senate candidates, fresh off Democratic primary victories, be enough of a catalyst for progressive change?
snippet: Can seven insurgent State Senate candidates, fresh off Democratic primary victories, be enough of a catalyst for progressive change?
lead_paragraph: They had already been hailed as courageous reformers, the insurgent candidates who dared take on New York State senators laden with money, influence and name recognition.

abstract: Ego Nwodim will join “S.N.L.” as a featured performer for the coming season, and the rest of its ensemble cast will return largely intact.
snippet: Ego Nwodim will join “S.N.L.” as a featured performer for the coming season, and the rest of its ensemble cast will return largely intact.
lead_paragraph: “Saturday Night Live” will return this season with its ensemble largely intact and just one new cast member: Ego Nwodim, a veteran of the UCB Theater in Los Angeles who has appeared on shows like “2 Broke Girls” and the “Law & Order True Crime” mini-series, will join “S.N.L.” as a featured performer, NBC announced on Friday.

headline_main: ‘Saturday Night Live’ Adds New Cast Member for 44th Season

abstract: Mr. Cuomo has described Joseph Percoco as “my father’s third son.” Now, Mr. Percoco’s conviction looms over Mr. Cuomo’s future.
snippet: Mr. Cuomo has described Joseph Percoco as “my father’s third son.” Now, Mr. Percoco’s conviction looms over Mr. Cuomo’s future.
lead_paragraph: Joseph Percoco, a former top adviser and confidant to Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo, was sentenced to six years in prison on Thursday in a case that cast a long and unflattering shadow over the Cuomo administration.
